Cloning issues that are with completed sprint value will inherit the value and can't be removed from UI.

The cloned issues however won't show up in the completed sprint reports.

h4. Workaround 1
Remove the sprint value from its field via JIRA issue navigator bulk edit:
# search for the affected issues in the Issue Navigator;
# click *Tools > Bulk Edit*;
# select the issue and click *Next*, then select *Edit Issues* and click *Next*;
# select _Change Sprint_ and edit the value accordingly - if you don't want the issue to be associated with any sprints, leave the field empty;
# click *Next* and proceed with the instructions to complete the change.

h4.Workaround 2:
- [Clear Sprint information when cloning JIRA issue | https://confluence.atlassian.com/jirakb/clear-sprint-information-when-cloning-jira-issue-779159157.html]

h3. Steps to reproduce

# Create an Epic;
# Associate an issue to this Epic and create a subtask under this issue;
# Create a board filtering for this Epic Link, like this:
{noformat}
"Epic Link" = Test
{noformat}
# Once the board is created, create a new sprint and start it;
# Open the board's work tab and check that the subtasks are not appearing;

h3. Current behaviour

Filtering for Epics hide the subtasks in the Work mode.

h3. Expected behaviour

Show the subtasks normally when the board's filter is based on an Epic.

h3. Steps to reproduce

# In a Scrum board, create a backlog content the is longer than a page size (so the scroll bar is created);
# Hold one of the tickets in order to reorganize it in the backlog/sprint;
# Scroll the mouse while holding the ticket;

h3. Current behaviour

The mouse scroll doesn't work and the only possibility is to drag the ticket to the top or to the bottom of the plan mode so the screen automatically scrolls. For small backlogs this isn't a problem, but for big backlogs (100+ issues) it can be time consuming to wait for the automatic scroll.

h3. Expected behaviour

Allow the mouse scroll behaviour to work while holding a ticket in the backlog.

As reported at https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/AGILE/JIRA+Agile+6.3.9.2+Release+Notes?focusedCommentId=550109398#comment-550109398

{quote}
We're seeing something else weird on subtasks, that could be related to the display of the sprint field within the edit issue dialog.

For example we have an issue with a couple of subtasks scheduled in sprint.  If you go to the edit screen for one of these subtasks and click update (regardless of whether or not you change any values as part of the edit), the subtask's history (and the email notification) will tell you that the sprint value was emptied.  (The subtasks issue detail screen still shows it as belonging to the correct sprint, and it still shows up on the scrum board's work area).  We're on JIRA 6.2, and see the above with both agile 6.3.9.1 and 6.3.9.2 (we never downloaded 6.3.9).{quote}
